cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the energy efficiency of a network enabled by unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and investigates joint caching and cooperative communication. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates an optimization problem for optimally assigning contents to caches and choosing the height of UAVs, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and coding theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with managing the energy expenditure of UAVs, which can be seen as a control problem. The optimization problem also involves constraints on the energy consumption of UAVs, which can be modeled using control theory.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes content placement strategies with low computational complexity, which falls under the scope of distributed computing.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with caching popular contents, which can be multimedia content such as videos and images. The optimization problem also involves the main communication/physical characteristics of UAVs, which can be related to multimedia transmission.
